      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Adding high-end amenities to Option C would certainly shift its perception toward luxury, but it wouldn't erase the fundamental difference in its core identity. A client looking for \"prestigious and culturally refined\" might see Option A as inherently superior because its refinement is built into its traditional structure, not layered on top of a different cultural base. The \"soulful\" aspect of Option C is tied to its roots, and while upscale shops can add money, they don't automatically equate to the established, old-money pedigree that the phrase \"culturally refined\" often implies in a Western luxury context.",
